Defendant Andrew C Juozapaitis in court with attorney Matthew Huppertz.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The State moves to amend count #1 to a county ordinance of disorderly conduct.  The Court amends accordingly, enters a no contest plea and finds the Defendant guilty.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.   The Defendant was sentenced as follows:

Count # 1:

FINE: $430.50 (to be paid in 60 days or serve 9 days jail, consecutive, as penalty for non payment of fine);
